<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-25T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.61333/955: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-25T15:00:00-03:00">March 25,
                                    1944—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1135. Embassy’s telegram 1047, March 20, 7 p.m.<note n="87" xml:id="d591fn87">Not printed.</note> The Minister of Finance has
                            agreed to recommend to President Vargas termination of the coffee
                            agreement and the ship deal. The latter was referred to him because of
                            its connection with the coffee transaction. He promised to send the
                            papers to the Foreign Office and President Vargas next week.</p>
                        <p>Both the Minister of Finance and Penteado, who is scheduled to arrive in
                            Washington within a few days, are greatly concerned over a probable
                            increase in coffee quotas.…</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>